review_blob:

Overall I really like it, gets me into the Christmas spirit.

Aroma: bread, roasty, hay, grass, floral, citrus, dough, 
Appearance: golden, clear, rocky head, 
Taste: light sweetness, medium bitterness, lightly sour, umami, 
Palate:light body, slick feel, lively, bitter, 
AWESOME! One of my favorites. Great Divide Brewing Co. makes some great brews.

Aroma: caramel, bread, roasty, resin, dough, smoke, 
Appearance: red, brown, clear, minimal head, 
Taste: medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, 
Palate: medium body, slick feel, soft carbonation, long finish, 
Overall it is a good beer, but Im not sure about mixing two different beers to make a whole new mixture. Somehow I think Im a purist in that way and prefer to keep them as individual brews.

Aroma: toast, resin, basement aromas, 
Appearance: golden, amber, clear, frothy, 
Taste: light sweetness, very bitter, medium sourness, umami,
Palate: light body, thin feel, fizzy, lively, bitter, long finish, 
Overall I thought this beer was one of the better ones that Granite City had. I really love IPAs and really liked this one even though the depth of the flavor profile wasnt a deep as I would have liked.

Aroma: hay, floral, grass, dough, alcohol, 
Appearance: pale, golden, clear, sparkling, 
Taste:light sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, 
Palate:light body, thin feel, fizzy, bitter, 
Overall it is an "average" beer to me something comparable to a bud light or a coors light with a bit more flavor.
-JK

Aroma; bread, grass, floral,

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob:
Aroma; caramel, coffee, roasty, resin, basement aromas, earthy, woody, 
Appearance; black, clear, frothy, tan foam, 
Taste; light sweetness, medium sourness, medium bitterness, 
Palate; medium body, thin feel, fizzy, bitter, 
Overall it is an interesting beer in that I like the more coffee and caramel flavors, whoever the drinkability for me is not the best. Not one of my favorites and wouldnt recommend it.

Aroma;caramel, herbs, clove, 
Appearance; red, clear, frothy, 
Taste; medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, umami, 
Palate; medium body, creamy, average carbonation, long finish 
Overall I really liked this beer its thicker more stout consistency was nice and got me in the fall spirit. I would highly recommend this beer.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Fall Hornin Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Can definitely smell the pumpkin along with, allspice, hay, citrus, and clove. It has a clear amber color with minimal head. heavy cloying sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, umami, medium body, slick feel, lively carbonation, with a long finish. Even though this beer is on the sweet side I enjoyed it very much with its balance of sweet and bitterness I would really recommend this beer.
very crisp hay/bread aroma, beautiful cloudy golden color, with a very crisp hay taste, lightly tart/bitter and medium-heavy body, lively carbination, and a bitter finish
